00:22:09.020 --> 00:22:12.110 align:middle line:84%
when I was ushered
up through a portal,

00:22:12.110 --> 00:22:15.680 align:middle line:84%
through a circle of
light, a melody of sound,

00:22:15.680 --> 00:22:19.510 align:middle line:84%
into a brilliant, ultra-real
valley, the gateway valley.

00:22:19.510 --> 00:22:23.150 align:middle line:84%
A lot of earthly features, but
it was like a world of ideals.

00:22:23.150 --> 00:22:24.920 align:middle line:90%
Everything was perfect.

00:22:24.920 --> 00:22:28.970 align:middle line:84%
And encountering higher
souls and guardian angels,

00:22:28.970 --> 00:22:32.380 align:middle line:84%
all that was perfectly
real in that realm.

00:22:32.380 --> 00:22:37.640 align:middle line:90%


00:22:37.640 --> 00:22:40.910 align:middle line:84%
>> I wanted to see if the
near-death experience was just

00:22:40.910 --> 00:22:44.020 align:middle line:84%
some form of hallucination as
the brain was shutting down.

00:22:44.020 --> 00:22:48.090 align:middle line:90%


00:22:48.090 --> 00:22:50.400 align:middle line:84%
What I kind of found
with my research

00:22:50.400 --> 00:22:52.710 align:middle line:84%
is that some people
gained information,

00:22:52.710 --> 00:22:54.600 align:middle line:84%
in ways other than
through the senses,

00:22:54.600 --> 00:22:56.520 align:middle line:84%
that they weren't
previously aware of.

00:22:56.520 --> 00:22:59.790 align:middle line:90%


00:22:59.790 --> 00:23:02.100 align:middle line:84%
One of the patients
in my study, he

00:23:02.100 --> 00:23:04.230 align:middle line:84%
met one of his
deceased relatives.

00:23:04.230 --> 00:23:07.140 align:middle line:84%
And as part of his
near-death experience,

00:23:07.140 --> 00:23:08.430 align:middle line:90%
she gave him a message.

00:23:08.430 --> 00:23:10.275 align:middle line:84%
And she said, you've
got to go back to life.

00:23:10.275 --> 00:23:14.700 align:middle line:84%
And when you go back, tell
this relative this message.

00:23:14.700 --> 00:23:17.520 align:middle line:84%
So when he did revive,
he gave this message

00:23:17.520 --> 00:23:19.200 align:middle line:90%
to the living relative.

00:23:19.200 --> 00:23:21.090 align:middle line:84%
And she was absolutely
astounded that he

00:23:21.090 --> 00:23:22.590 align:middle line:90%
should know that information.

00:23:22.590 --> 00:23:25.950 align:middle line:84%
>> To me, as a conventional
neuroscientist,

00:23:25.950 --> 00:23:29.250 align:middle line:84%
that absolutely demanded
some explanation because it

00:23:29.250 --> 00:23:32.610 align:middle line:84%
completely defied everything
that modern neuroscience thinks

00:23:32.610 --> 00:23:35.760 align:middle line:84%
it knows about the
neocortex, and the brain,

00:23:35.760 --> 00:23:39.680 align:middle line:84%
and its relationship
to consciousness.

00:23:39.680 --> 00:23:44.420 align:middle line:84%
>> I don't think the near-death
experience is a brain

00:23:44.420 --> 00:23:45.470 align:middle line:90%
phenomenon.

00:23:45.470 --> 00:23:47.870 align:middle line:10%
I think it's wider than that.

00:23:47.870 --> 00:23:49.580 align:middle line:84%
I think what
happens is the brain

00:23:49.580 --> 00:23:54.410 align:middle line:84%
in some way is compromised,
either through fear

00:23:54.410 --> 00:23:59.240 align:middle line:84%
or through damage, and during
that the image of the body

00:23:59.240 --> 00:24:03.770 align:middle line:84%
somehow deteriorates within the
brain and this new form arises.

00:24:03.770 --> 00:24:07.990 align:middle line:90%


00:24:07.990 --> 00:24:10.960 align:middle line:10%
>> People tend to lose fear
of death after near-death

00:24:10.960 --> 00:24:12.322 align:middle line:10%
experiences.

00:24:12.322 --> 00:24:13.780 align:middle line:10%
And I think fear
of death in itself

00:24:13.780 --> 00:24:15.930 align:middle line:10%
is extremely transformational.

00:24:15.930 --> 00:24:18.070 align:middle line:84%
Once you lose fear
of death, everything

00:24:18.070 --> 00:24:21.500 align:middle line:90%
changes in your life.

00:24:21.500 --> 00:24:23.870 align:middle line:90%
>> No fear of death.

00:24:23.870 --> 00:24:25.400 align:middle line:90%
I know this is not it.

00:24:25.400 --> 00:24:28.460 align:middle line:84%
And it's not nothing that
somebody has told me.

00:24:28.460 --> 00:24:30.330 align:middle line:84%
It's something that
I've experienced myself,

00:24:30.330 --> 00:24:32.270 align:middle line:84%
so that's a truth that
nobody can take away.

00:24:32.270 --> 00:24:35.250 align:middle line:90%


00:24:35.250 --> 00:24:42.700 align:middle line:84%
>> But then I suppose I was kind
of in the you're born, you die,

00:24:42.700 --> 00:24:46.110 align:middle line:90%
and that's it kind of group.

00:24:46.110 --> 00:24:51.280 align:middle line:84%
Today I'm a bit like you're
born, you die, and that's it?

00:24:51.280 --> 00:24:55.560 align:middle line:84%
Do people still believe
that mumbo jumbo?

00:24:55.560 --> 00:24:57.653 align:middle line:84%
>> It definitely
confirmed it for me.

00:24:57.653 --> 00:24:59.820 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, you believe it, but
you don't-- look, with me,

00:24:59.820 --> 00:25:01.403 align:middle line:84%
I have to see something
to believe it.

00:25:01.403 --> 00:25:03.330 align:middle line:84%
I have to see it, and
then I'm like, OK.

00:25:03.330 --> 00:25:06.660 align:middle line:84%
And I've seen so much
now that I have no doubt

00:25:06.660 --> 00:25:08.703 align:middle line:84%
that when you die it's
just your physical body

00:25:08.703 --> 00:25:09.620 align:middle line:90%
you're leaving behind.

00:25:09.620 --> 00:25:11.003 align:middle line:90%
But it's your consciousness--

00:25:11.003 --> 00:25:12.420 align:middle line:84%
when people say
your soul, you can

00:25:12.420 --> 00:25:15.240 align:middle line:84%
call it your soul, your astral
body, your consciousness,

00:25:15.240 --> 00:25:16.040 align:middle line:90%
it doesn't matter.

00:25:16.040 --> 00:25:16.860 align:middle line:90%
It's all one thing.

00:25:16.860 --> 00:25:22.350 align:middle line:84%
But it's that that
leaves, that goes on.

00:25:22.350 --> 00:25:26.340 align:middle line:84%
>> The most meaningful thing
to take away from out-of-body

00:25:26.340 --> 00:25:29.203 align:middle line:84%
experiences is that you're
more than your physical body.

00:25:29.203 --> 00:25:31.370 align:middle line:84%
>> Obviously, if I'm about
to get run over by a car,

00:25:31.370 --> 00:25:32.900 align:middle line:90%
I'm jumping out the way.

00:25:32.900 --> 00:25:36.410 align:middle line:84%
But I'm not afraid
for it to happen.

00:25:36.410 --> 00:25:40.100 align:middle line:84%
>> It brings acceptance of
life, acceptance of the reality

00:25:40.100 --> 00:25:42.290 align:middle line:90%
of life and of death.

00:25:42.290 --> 00:25:46.616 align:middle line:84%
So that feeling of acceptance
is incredibly transformational.

00:25:46.616 --> 00:25:49.056 align:middle line:90%
[ELECTRONIC MUSIC]

00:25:49.056 --> 00:25:58.330 align:middle line:90%


00:25:58.330 --> 00:26:02.360 align:middle line:84%
>> DMT, often called
the spirit molecule,

00:26:02.360 --> 00:26:05.390 align:middle line:84%
is a chemical substance found
within almost all plants

00:26:05.390 --> 00:26:06.720 align:middle line:90%
and animals.

00:26:06.720 --> 00:26:10.130 align:middle line:84%
Some people have claimed that
near-death-like experiences

00:26:10.130 --> 00:26:12.800 align:middle line:90%
can result from ingesting DMT.

00:26:12.800 --> 00:26:14.750 align:middle line:84%
But are they really
the same thing?

00:26:14.750 --> 00:26:17.770 align:middle line:90%


00:26:17.770 --> 00:26:21.100 align:middle line:84%
>> Near-death experiences are
typically more kind of earthly

00:26:21.100 --> 00:26:21.980 align:middle line:90%
in their origin.

00:26:21.980 --> 00:26:26.560 align:middle line:10%
So you may see the room itself,
and perhaps your body in it

00:26:26.560 --> 00:26:29.210 align:middle line:10%
