00:26:32.280 --> 00:26:40.870 align:middle line:84%
altogether, a world composed
of energy, and geometry,

00:26:40.870 --> 00:26:42.370 align:middle line:90%
and strange beings.

00:26:42.370 --> 00:26:43.990 align:middle line:10%
So it's an
out-of-body experience

00:26:43.990 --> 00:26:47.380 align:middle line:10%
of a kind, which if you tick
a box on a questionnaire

00:26:47.380 --> 00:26:51.340 align:middle line:10%
looks similar, but
phenomenalogically

00:26:51.340 --> 00:26:56.420 align:middle line:10%
the actual content of the
experience is very different.

00:26:56.420 --> 00:27:00.580 align:middle line:84%
>> The similarities between DMT
experiences and NDEs are quite

00:27:00.580 --> 00:27:02.020 align:middle line:90%
limited.

00:27:02.020 --> 00:27:04.210 align:middle line:84%
And most of the
powerful features,

00:27:04.210 --> 00:27:06.250 align:middle line:84%
the most striking
features of NDEs,

00:27:06.250 --> 00:27:08.260 align:middle line:84%
do not feature in
DMT experiences,

00:27:08.260 --> 00:27:10.820 align:middle line:84%
like the life review,
or the contact

00:27:10.820 --> 00:27:13.755 align:middle line:84%
with deceased relatives, or
the sense of entering a tunnel,

00:27:13.755 --> 00:27:15.810 align:middle line:90%
and so on.

00:27:15.810 --> 00:27:18.600 align:middle line:10%
>> DMT is also one of those
substances will induce

00:27:18.600 --> 00:27:20.198 align:middle line:10%
out-of-body experiences.

00:27:20.198 --> 00:27:21.990 align:middle line:10%
Perhaps not to the same
extent as ketamine,

00:27:21.990 --> 00:27:26.130 align:middle line:10%
but there are some
differences, however.

00:27:26.130 --> 00:27:29.070 align:middle line:84%
DMT experiences
often are concurrent

00:27:29.070 --> 00:27:31.680 align:middle line:84%
with geometric patterns
or the encounters

00:27:31.680 --> 00:27:33.870 align:middle line:84%
with pixies and elves,
which you don't typically

00:27:33.870 --> 00:27:35.652 align:middle line:90%
get on out-of-body experiences.

00:27:35.652 --> 00:27:37.110 align:middle line:10%
It can help us,
perhaps though, try

00:27:37.110 --> 00:27:39.090 align:middle line:10%
and explain
out-of-body experiences

00:27:39.090 --> 00:27:42.210 align:middle line:10%
because DMT is naturally
occurring in the human body.

00:27:42.210 --> 00:27:43.770 align:middle line:84%
But there's not a
1-to-1 relationship

00:27:43.770 --> 00:27:45.180 align:middle line:90%
between the two experiences.

00:27:45.180 --> 00:27:48.810 align:middle line:90%


00:27:48.810 --> 00:27:50.860 align:middle line:84%
>> The doors of perception
was William Blake,

00:27:50.860 --> 00:27:53.470 align:middle line:84%
the idea that our perceptions
only give us a very small part

00:27:53.470 --> 00:27:54.270 align:middle line:90%
of reality.

00:27:54.270 --> 00:27:57.360 align:middle line:84%
But sometimes, with
mind-altering substances--

00:27:57.360 --> 00:28:00.330 align:middle line:84%
dimethyltryptamine, for
instance, as an example--

00:28:00.330 --> 00:28:02.830 align:middle line:84%
suddenly it broadens out,
and the doors of perception

00:28:02.830 --> 00:28:03.630 align:middle line:90%
are opened.

00:28:03.630 --> 00:28:07.890 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly our
perceptions are much wider.

00:28:07.890 --> 00:28:12.570 align:middle line:84%
>> One particular experience I
had was deeply profound in that

00:28:12.570 --> 00:28:14.910 align:middle line:84%
