back, I came back

00:28:17.550 --> 00:28:20.530 align:middle line:84%
and I could see these
strange creatures.

00:28:20.530 --> 00:28:21.660 align:middle line:90%
And I was like, whoa.

00:28:21.660 --> 00:28:24.280 align:middle line:10%
And then I realized I was
looking at myself and my friend

00:28:24.280 --> 00:28:25.080 align:middle line:10%
on the floor.

00:28:25.080 --> 00:28:27.285 align:middle line:10%
For me, it was deeply profound.

00:28:27.285 --> 00:28:30.780 align:middle line:90%


00:28:30.780 --> 00:28:33.480 align:middle line:10%
I'd say that experience
has influenced my thinking

00:28:33.480 --> 00:28:37.680 align:middle line:10%
about the nature of reality
in that I'm certainly

00:28:37.680 --> 00:28:40.170 align:middle line:10%
very open to the idea
that consciousness is

00:28:40.170 --> 00:28:44.100 align:middle line:10%
a separate entity to the body.

00:28:44.100 --> 00:28:46.860 align:middle line:84%
>> In 2002, when a
neuroscientist called Olaf

00:28:46.860 --> 00:28:49.980 align:middle line:84%
Blanke was operating on
an epileptic patient,

00:28:49.980 --> 00:28:53.158 align:middle line:84%
with electrodes
all over the brain,

00:28:53.158 --> 00:28:54.825 align:middle line:84%
and he could stimulate
different places.

00:28:54.825 --> 00:28:57.990 align:middle line:90%


00:28:57.990 --> 00:28:59.810 align:middle line:10%
And he discovered
that if he stimulated

00:28:59.810 --> 00:29:02.340 align:middle line:10%
a spot on the right
