00:29:02.340 --> 00:29:05.460 align:middle line:10%
he could produce bodily
distortions or, at the extreme,

00:29:05.460 --> 00:29:09.840 align:middle line:10%
a complete out-of-body
experience.

00:29:09.840 --> 00:29:13.580 align:middle line:84%
So we know that that spot,
disturbed, can produce

00:29:13.580 --> 00:29:14.940 align:middle line:90%
an out-of-body experience.

00:29:14.940 --> 00:29:15.740 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:29:15.740 --> 00:29:20.870 align:middle line:90%


00:29:20.870 --> 00:29:24.800 align:middle line:84%
>> Those studies that have
tried to induce out-of-body

00:29:24.800 --> 00:29:28.670 align:middle line:84%
experience through electric
stimulation or neuromodulation,

00:29:28.670 --> 00:29:30.320 align:middle line:90%
they are very interesting.

00:29:30.320 --> 00:29:34.910 align:middle line:84%
But the question is
does that mimic, really,

00:29:34.910 --> 00:29:37.290 align:middle line:90%
the real experience or not?

00:29:37.290 --> 00:29:41.000 align:middle line:84%
Because when you are stimulating
areas of the brain associated

00:29:41.000 --> 00:29:43.670 align:middle line:84%
with smell, the person
is, for example,

00:29:43.670 --> 00:29:45.930 align:middle line:84%
