00:29:48.770 --> 00:29:54.980 align:middle line:84%
But the person can record,
and can even smell,

00:29:54.980 --> 00:29:56.480 align:middle line:84%
or have the impression
of the smell.

00:29:56.480 --> 00:30:01.070 align:middle line:90%


00:30:01.070 --> 00:30:03.920 align:middle line:84%
>> The area of the brain
that is stimulating produces

00:30:03.920 --> 00:30:07.190 align:middle line:84%
an experience that's not
very consistent with the type

00:30:07.190 --> 00:30:10.070 align:middle line:84%
of experiences people have,
what I would consider a genuine

00:30:10.070 --> 00:30:11.540 align:middle line:90%
out-of-body experience.

00:30:11.540 --> 00:30:14.570 align:middle line:84%
So a sense of moving
over a distance,

00:30:14.570 --> 00:30:18.350 align:middle line:84%
going to another location,
perceiving things accurately

00:30:18.350 --> 00:30:20.060 align:middle line:90%
that are happening around them--

00:30:20.060 --> 00:30:22.760 align:middle line:84%
things like that don't
happen in these kinds

00:30:22.760 --> 00:30:27.860 align:middle line:84%
of induced experiences using the
TPJ, temporoparietal junction.

00:30:27.860 --> 00:30:31.970 align:middle line:90%


00:30:31.970 --> 00:30:36.110 align:middle line:84%
>> There are places you can
stimulate the brain to mimic

00:30:36.110 --> 00:30:40.490 align:middle line:84%
certain experiences, but
one should not be confused

00:30:40.490 --> 00:30:45.170 align:middle line:84%
by thinking that those kinds
of tricks and various ways

00:30:45.170 --> 00:30:48.950 align:middle line:84%
of demonstrating relationships
between some types

00:30:48.950 --> 00:30:51.740 align:middle line:84%
of electrical or magnetic
stimulation and phenomenal

00:30:51.740 --> 00:30:54.380 align:middle line:84%
experience, that you can
then assume, oh, well,

00:30:54.380 --> 00:30:56.520 align:middle line:90%
that's the cause of all of them.

00:30:56.520 --> 00:31:00.020 align:middle line:84%
And that's one of
the biggest mistakes.

00:31:00.020 --> 00:31:02.420 align:middle line:84%
>> So the types of things
that happen are not really

00:31:02.420 --> 00:31:04.400 align:middle line:84%
consistent with an
out-of-body experience,

00:31:04.400 --> 00:31:07.850 align:middle line:84%
which is essentially what I
think many of the skeptics do.

00:31:07.850 --> 00:31:09.710 align:middle line:84%
They use this what
I would consider

00:31:09.710 --> 00:31:12.890 align:middle line:84%
overly broad definition,
which then means

00:31:12.890 --> 00:31:14.900 align:middle line:84%
that you could pretty
much define anything

00:31:14.900 --> 00:31:16.550 align:middle line:90%
as an out-of-body experience.

00:31:16.550 --> 00:31:20.360 align:middle line:84%
>> How real is this phenomena
that is induced by this

00:31:20.360 --> 00:31:21.898 align:middle line:90%
electric stimulation?

00:31:21.898 --> 00:31:23.440 align:middle line:84%
Because you can say
that you are just

00:31:23.440 --> 00:31:27.830 align:middle line:84%
stimulating the impression of
it, not the real phenomena.

00:31:27.830 --> 00:31:30.290 align:middle line:84%
That is what we would
think is related

00:31:30.290 --> 00:31:31.522 align:middle line:90%
to out-of-body experience.

00:31:31.522 --> 00:31:33.980 align:middle line:84%
>> I don't think the experiences
are caused by neurological

00:31:33.980 --> 00:31:35.570 align:middle line:90%
activity.

00:31:35.570 --> 00:31:39.080 align:middle line:84%
I think they happen at a
level beyond the brain.

00:31:39.080 --> 00:31:43.263 align:middle line:90%


00:31:43.263 --> 00:31:45.055 align:middle line:84%
If there are any brain
changes, any changes

00:31:45.055 --> 00:31:47.120 align:middle line:84%
to neurological activity,
they are produced

00:31:47.120 --> 00:31:49.045 align:middle line:90%
by the change in consciousness.

00:31:49.045 --> 00:31:53.410 align:middle line:90%


00:31:53.410 --> 00:31:57.610 align:middle line:84%
>> My view of consciousness
is that it's not created

00:31:57.610 --> 00:32:00.730 align:middle line:84%
by the brain, that the
