my eyes, thank goodness.

00:35:33.420 --> 00:35:35.820 align:middle line:84%
But I only sometimes
have those experiences.

00:35:35.820 --> 00:35:38.880 align:middle line:84%
They're on the cutting
edge of where we're going.

00:35:38.880 --> 00:35:43.410 align:middle line:84%
It's kind of a new possibility
that hasn't really--

00:35:43.410 --> 00:35:45.700 align:middle line:84%
some people better than
others, all that stuff.

00:35:45.700 --> 00:35:47.380 align:middle line:90%
That's the first reason.

00:35:47.380 --> 00:35:50.340 align:middle line:84%
The second reason is
science only looks

00:35:50.340 --> 00:35:51.780 align:middle line:90%
at the sensual world.

00:35:51.780 --> 00:35:54.420 align:middle line:84%
So it says that doesn't
exist, or that's just

00:35:54.420 --> 00:35:55.740 align:middle line:90%
an illusion or a byproduct.

00:35:55.740 --> 00:35:58.040 align:middle line:84%
So it dismisses
it theoretically,

00:35:58.040 --> 00:36:00.690 align:middle line:84%
and therefore it doesn't want
to look at it, which is a shame.

00:36:00.690 --> 00:36:03.210 align:middle line:84%
Because the odd things are
where the new understanding

00:36:03.210 --> 00:36:04.920 align:middle line:90%
will come from.

00:36:04.920 --> 00:36:09.090 align:middle line:84%
And the third thing is,
in the causal world,

00:36:09.090 --> 00:36:12.940 align:middle line:84%
the material world, you can
reproduce things, generally.

00:36:12.940 --> 00:36:15.800 align:middle line:84%
